result.name: Peking Garden Restaurant

reviews.text: I always go to this restaurant while I am in Hong Kong but my recent visit is the last time I would ever dine there again!  Typical HK restaurant rule of two hours dining time on Sunday and I am fine with that.  However, we waited 45 minutes until the first dish of food came to our table and other dishes arrived slowly after that.  Two hours passed and the server even asked us to pay the bill before all the orders arrived.  It's the restaurant's fault taking over two hours serving our food slowly but the staffs there think it is our responsibility to have two hours usage on the table even they served food slowly.  That's the worst customer service in the world!  I was able to give the table back in two hours before but this is the first time the restaurant putting their mistake on customers!  Totally not impressed!

Too crowded with people passing from mtr station if you sit on the outside of the tables. And usually you’d better book in advance.
Anyway beijing duck was amazing!
Delicious as ever. Peaking Garden is an institution in Central HK for their delicious peaking duck.
Great restaurant, in a convenient location, and with fair price given the high quality of food and service. Incorrectly listed as "Permanently Closed".

Need a booking on Friday night, busy but service was quick and up to standard, the tables were not too close so noise was not a problem. The set meal with sea cucumber and abalone was great. Don't miss the Peking duck!
Nice modern mall to spend time in. Clean toilets and environment
Beautiful and modern
Location is great, crowded but worth visiting for shopping and food.
Very good mid-upscale shopping mall.  The mall hosts nice exhibits every now and then. Currently, it’s the Spiral Scratch by Jim Lambie.
A great place to be especially during Christmas.
